long_description: hey, it's back to school time at little feet , denver's premiere children's shoe store. we carry karamel corn, minnetonka, cienta, and primigi slippers, there's so many to choose from. let's face it, kids love crocs. drewson is the newest style from crocs, it looks like a sneaker with an easy-on velcro strap, and has the lightweight feel that crocs are known for. these handy little gadgets attach to your child's shoes to help them tie their shoes on their own. the fun designs like dragons, butterflies and smiley faces are a fun addition to any lace up shoe. lightweight canvas shoes made in spain. umi morie is a fun slip on moccasin style for girls. we are denver 's premiere children's shoe store. at our family owned and operated business, fitting expertise and footwear knowledge have been passed down from one generation to the next. we like to blog about all things related to little feet. this is our place to share tips, advice and fun facts about kids' feet and current shoe styles. of course, we would love for our "virtual conversation" to turn into an "in-person conversation" as well.
